author: Dana Scott
title: Crazy Tigers Fans Grilled Real Alligators Before LSU-Florida Game
text:
As the LSU Tigers face the Florida Gators tonight , both of these top 10-ranked SEC teams have a bone to pick with each other. But for some LSU fans who tailgated before the kickoff, they have more to pick from between their teeth- alligators scales, that is.
This looks like a delicacy to some crazy people who like eating reptiles . Here are the reactions from some who partook in the Creole alligator souffle.
Alligator is on the pit. #LSU #Florida #GameDay pic.twitter.com/Kc4W4anrLc
— Michelle (@Mimo1001) October 17, 2015 @JacquesDoucet @WAFB come see us! pic.twitter.com/kJKLqVMrjA
— Brantley Salter (@brantleysalter) October 17, 2015 #LSU fans cooking up Gator on campus. @WAFB pic.twitter.com/BW8ReqZZ32
— Jacques Doucet (@JacquesDoucet) October 17, 2015 @JacquesDoucet @WAFB come see us! pic.twitter.com/kJKLqVMrjA
— Brantley Salter (@brantleysalter) October 17, 2015 Ummm, yum?? Gotta love fans who take rivalries literally about smoking their opponents.
